00:48:29,080 --> 00:48:33,360
They didn't even know that we couldn't sit in the same rooms

1012
00:48:33,360 --> 00:48:34,760
when we go to the doctor.

1013
00:48:34,760 --> 00:48:38,400
They had separate colors on one side and white on the other

1014
00:48:38,400 --> 00:48:39,000
side.

1015
00:48:39,000 --> 00:48:41,440
A lot of these kids today don't know that because things

1016
00:48:41,440 --> 00:48:42,920
ain't already happened.

1017
00:48:42,920 --> 00:48:45,800
We had already suffered through it and got it for them.

1018
00:48:45,800 --> 00:48:46,640
And they just don't.

1019
00:48:46,640 --> 00:48:50,720
I think we need to make sure they get more history.

1020
00:48:50,720 --> 00:48:52,800
What going on it might be make the whole thing.

1021
00:48:52,800 --> 00:48:56,120
But see, now in school, they don't give it to them.

1022
00:48:56,120 --> 00:48:57,840
Was that something you tried to push on while you were

1023
00:48:57,840 --> 00:48:58,880
on the school board?

1024
00:48:58,880 --> 00:49:02,320
Yeah, but we have a wonderful program.

1025
00:49:02,320 --> 00:49:03,800
And nothing else about it.

1026
00:49:03,800 --> 00:49:04,320
OK.

1027
00:49:04,320 --> 00:49:08,240
It's on the school year.

1028
00:49:08,240 --> 00:49:12,240
But I think it needs to be a lot of it.

1029
00:49:12,240 --> 00:49:14,520
Like kids should know the history.

1030
00:49:14,520 --> 00:49:15,720
Maybe they would do better.

1031
00:49:15,720 --> 00:49:16,220
OK.

1032
00:49:16,220 --> 00:49:17,400
We would do better.

1033
00:49:17,400 --> 00:49:18,400
OK.

1034
00:49:18,400 --> 00:49:20,880
And maybe the whole community would do better.

1035
00:49:20,880 --> 00:49:25,160
It would be more love if the younger, quiet and black would

1036
00:49:25,160 --> 00:49:27,520
know what happened.

1037
00:49:27,520 --> 00:49:31,440
Because I've seen a lot of them once, now that they wouldn't

1038
00:49:31,440 --> 00:49:35,080
come down nothing like that.

1039
00:49:35,080 --> 00:49:37,560
But they just don't know.

1040
00:49:37,560 --> 00:49:39,080
OK.

1041
00:49:39,080 --> 00:49:42,200
So about your experiences in Baker County,

1042
00:49:42,200 --> 00:49:44,280
that you think?

1043
00:49:44,280 --> 00:49:49,240
Well, all the things that I know, that I could say,

1044
00:49:49,240 --> 00:49:50,880
that I had a birthday.

1045
00:49:50,880 --> 00:49:52,760
I was 80 years old.

1046
00:49:52,760 --> 00:49:56,880
And I just thank God to be able to help in the community.

1047
00:49:56,880 --> 00:50:00,400
Because I don't think it's nobody if you go to have two

1048
00:50:00,400 --> 00:50:02,320
roles named after me.

1049
00:50:02,320 --> 00:50:05,560
The school role is named Grace Little Circus.

1050
00:50:05,560 --> 00:50:08,120
And the role, because by my house, it's named Grace Little

1051
00:50:08,120 --> 00:50:09,000
Road.

1052
00:50:09,000 --> 00:50:13,560
So I just don't think, but I didn't wait till I die.

1053
00:50:13,560 --> 00:50:15,720
They did it while I'm alive.

1054
00:50:15,720 --> 00:50:19,640
I got to smell some of the flowers while I'm alive.

1055
00:50:19,640 --> 00:50:22,960
And I'm just so happy over there.

1056
00:50:22,960 --> 00:50:26,600
You don't know really how you touch other people's lives

1057
00:50:26,600 --> 00:50:28,840
until they let you know.

1058
00:50:28,840 --> 00:50:32,240
So I feel like I have done my best.

1059
00:50:32,240 --> 00:50:34,680
If I don't do any more, I feel like I have done my best

1060
00:50:34,680 --> 00:50:35,680
for that county.

1061
00:50:35,680 --> 00:50:36,180
OK.

1062
00:50:36,180 --> 00:50:39,000
So I've been on all kind of boards.

1063
00:50:39,000 --> 00:50:41,360
And I work honestly with them.

1064
00:50:41,360 --> 00:50:44,720
And I earned a respect from them.

1065
00:50:44,720 --> 00:50:46,800
And they have earned it for me.

1066
00:50:46,800 --> 00:50:47,320
OK.

1067
00:50:47,320 --> 00:50:50,600
Well, thank you so much, Mr. Miller, for pointing

1068
00:50:50,600 --> 00:50:51,200
on my question.

1069
00:50:51,200 --> 00:50:52,000
OK.

1070
00:50:52,000 --> 00:50:54,560
Could you tell me, John, me and just very shortly,

1071
00:50:54,560 --> 00:50:56,440
what the story of your daughter's problem

1072
00:50:56,440 --> 00:50:59,840
was in what her position was and what happened?

1073
00:50:59,840 --> 00:51:05,800
She was the first director of agriculture

1074
00:51:05,800 --> 00:51:08,720
of Ag and state of Georgia.

1075
00:51:08,720 --> 00:51:14,960
And I just feel like it was a thing out from the beginning.

1076
00:51:14,960 --> 00:51:18,160
Because while somebody had a meeting,

1077
00:51:18,160 --> 00:51:22,360
they knew she was speaking at this NACP meeting.

1078
00:51:22,360 --> 00:51:25,080
And while somebody had to sneak around

1079
00:51:25,080 --> 00:51:27,240
to try to get some information.

1080
00:51:27,240 --> 00:51:31,920
So I feel like it was sort of set up at this

1081
00:51:31,920 --> 00:51:34,040
like that she was in.

1082
00:51:34,040 --> 00:51:35,440
And that's my feeling about it.

1083
00:51:35,440 --> 00:51:38,880
And now people, that's the way I feel in my heart about it.

1084
00:51:38,880 --> 00:51:42,640
So the story was that she went to this NACP meeting

1085
00:51:42,640 --> 00:51:46,160
and gave a speech and spoke about it.

1086
00:51:46,160 --> 00:51:47,720
She was trying to convince the people

1087
00:51:47,720 --> 00:51:50,480
that how we need to come together.

1088
00:51:50,480 --> 00:51:54,600
And she said, if I can do it, I feel like it should be doing

1089
00:51:54,600 --> 00:51:56,400
because anybody else could do,

1090
00:51:56,400 --> 00:52:00,960
was her father got killed by a white man when she was young.

1091
00:52:00,960 --> 00:52:03,720
And she forgave and she tried to help.

1092
00:52:03,720 --> 00:52:06,840
Only thing she was just trying to say is that we need

1093
00:52:06,840 --> 00:52:08,440
to come together as a people.

1094
00:52:08,440 --> 00:52:11,280
And she told the story of the Spooner, the mayor,

1095
00:52:11,280 --> 00:52:11,960
Spooner who won.

1096
00:52:11,960 --> 00:52:13,760
And the Spooner heard it on the,

1097
00:52:13,760 --> 00:52:17,080
well, one of the songs that he was watching at TV.

1098
00:52:17,080 --> 00:52:19,120
And he told his mother, went up to the house

1099
00:52:19,120 --> 00:52:21,480
to tell his mother, the mother father said,

1100
00:52:21,480 --> 00:52:23,760
they got your friend in trouble.

1101
00:52:23,760 --> 00:52:25,200
They said, turn on TV.

1102
00:52:25,200 --> 00:52:27,160
And they turned on TV.

1103
00:52:27,160 --> 00:52:29,480
And he said, they tried to call.

1104
00:52:29,480 --> 00:52:32,080
And they couldn't get through, but they called CNN.

1105
00:52:32,080 --> 00:52:33,920
His song got CNN.

1106
00:52:33,920 --> 00:52:36,680
And he was at CNN, it was at her house.

1107
00:52:36,680 --> 00:52:40,600
And they told her, say, share this, I believe this is somebody

1108
00:52:40,600 --> 00:52:43,520
that you would love to talk to on the phone.

1109
00:52:43,520 --> 00:52:46,320
And they talked to them and let them

1110
00:52:46,320 --> 00:52:48,040
know that it was a lie.

1111
00:52:48,040 --> 00:52:50,160
They shared a hip thing.

1112
00:52:50,160 --> 00:52:54,160
Because she said they came to Harvard twice.

1113
00:52:54,160 --> 00:52:57,760
And the white guy they had, wasn't helpful.

1114
00:52:57,760 --> 00:53:00,880
But she found somebody to help them.

1115
00:53:00,880 --> 00:53:02,320
She said it was the last minute.

1116
00:53:02,320 --> 00:53:05,000
But whoever this guy that she got was her friend.

1117
00:53:05,000 --> 00:53:07,600
And they were looking for help to save the family.

1118
00:53:07,600 --> 00:53:08,200
Save the lives.

1119
00:53:08,200 --> 00:53:09,640
They found them.

1120
00:53:09,640 --> 00:53:12,280
And they own that farm now.

1121
00:53:12,280 --> 00:53:14,160
Because they had this birthday.

1122
00:53:14,160 --> 00:53:17,680
It was in November, because it was just getting cold.

1123
00:53:17,680 --> 00:53:18,520
Because that went down.

1124
00:53:18,520 --> 00:53:20,200
They wouldn't be coming with them.

1125
00:53:20,200 --> 00:53:24,280
And it's a beautiful place, then.

1126
00:53:24,280 --> 00:53:25,480
And they just so thankful.

1127
00:53:25,480 --> 00:53:26,960
They still have boys.

1128
00:53:26,960 --> 00:53:30,160
They all year round their father and mother.

1129
00:53:30,160 --> 00:53:31,520
And they just happened.

1130
00:53:31,520 --> 00:53:33,160
And they were able to save it.

1131
00:53:33,160 --> 00:53:35,240
And I'm so thankful to them that they came

1132
00:53:35,240 --> 00:53:36,200
for it.

1133
00:53:36,200 --> 00:53:37,440
It's the right time for her.

1134
00:53:42,040 --> 00:53:44,120
Thank you, Miss Miller again.

1135
00:53:44,120 --> 00:53:46,040
I hope I didn't.

1136
00:53:46,040 --> 00:53:49,160
This has been a presentation of the Library of Congress

1137
00:53:49,160 --> 00:53:51,280
and the Smithsonian National Museum

1138
00:53:51,280 --> 00:53:54,760
of African-American history and culture.

